          "line up": "Line up means to stand in a line with other people.",
          "interact": "Interact means to talk or do something with someone.",
          "cooperate": "Cooperate means to work together.",
          "beat": "Beat means to win against someone in a game or race.",
          "thumped": "Thumped means hit hard with a dull sound.",
          "bouncing": "Bouncing means moving up again after hitting a surface.",
          "stinks": "Stinks can mean something feels bad, unfair, or unpleasant.",
          "patient": "Patient means able to stay calm and wait.",
          "held her tongue": "Held her tongue means she stayed quiet and did not say the words she wanted to say.",
          "imagination": "Imagination is the power to make pictures or ideas in your mind.",
          "describe": "Describe means to say or write what something is like.",
          "entertained": "Entertained means kept people happy and interested.",
          "amused": "Amused means happy because something is funny or interesting.",
          "match": "Match means to be as good as someone or to keep up with them."
        },
